<h3>Show Notes:</h3>

<p>
	In this episode, Bekah and Dan talk about mental health with Cameron Bardell,
	an iOS developer in the healthcare industry, and Rahat Chowdhury, a mental
	health start-up founder. We talk about how sometimes building a product to
	meet our own needs is a great place to start and the importance of
	prioritizing mental health, especially in a fast-paced industry like tech. We
	walk through our own experiences, how mental health recovery isn't linear, and
	how different approaches to mental health technology create support for more
	people.
</p>

